TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Theory of Dissimilarity Between Stochastic Discount Factors
AU  - Bakshi, Gurdip
AU  - Gao, Xiaohui
AU  - Panayotov, George
Y1  - 2020/10/05
PY  - 2020
DA  - 2021/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.2020.3690
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.2020.3690
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 4602
EP  - 4622
VL  - 67
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper proposes a measure of dissimilarity between stochastic discount factors (SDFs) in different economies. The SDFs are made comparable using the respective bond prices as the numeraire. The measure is dimensionless, synthesizes features of the risk-neutral moments of excess currency returns, and can be extracted from currency option prices. Linking theory to data, we provide evidence gathered from (i) the cross section of 45 currency option prices, (ii) the time series of currency returns, (iii) estimated SDFs using model-free restrictions, and (iv) structural models in international finance. This paper was accepted by David Simchi-Levi, finance.
